DTSTAMP:20260724T114943Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260930
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261001
SUMMARY:Deadline: We Are Human Festival 2026: Call for Films (Paris)
DESCRIPTION:Call for short films (1-10 minutes) involving human/AI hybrid c
 reation\, from the We Are Human Foundation in Paris. Three cash awards: Gr
 and Prix EUR 5\,000\, Best Screenplay EUR 3\,000\, and an Ethics Award EUR
  2\,000. ELIGIBILITY: international\, applicants 18+\; films must have bee
 n completed after 1 June 2025 and involve human/AI hybrid creation\; a man
 datory Ethics Notebook accompanies each submission. No submission fee. Fes
 tival screening at Forum des images\, Paris\, on 24 November 2026. Apply v
 ia FilmFreeway\; deadline 30 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: We Are Human
  Foundation\nLocation: Paris\, France (Forum des images screening 24 Novem
 ber 2026)\nAward: Grand Prix EUR 5\,000\; Best Screenplay EUR 3\,000\; Eth
 ics Award EUR 2\,000. No submission fee.\nDuration: Annual short-film fest
 ival (screening 24 November 2026)\n\nMore: https://wearehuman.foundation/e
 n/call-for-films/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
URL:https://wearehuman.foundation/en/call-for-films/?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Paris\, France (Forum des images screening 24 November 2026)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hibrides-biennial-artistic-research-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114943Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260907
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260908
SUMMARY:Deadline: Híbrides: Small Embodied Data - Call for Contributions (
 2nd Edition)
DESCRIPTION:Híbrides is a biennial of artistic research co-organised by th
 e Axolot.cat collective and the DARTS (Design\, Art\, Technology and Socie
 ty) research group at the UOC in Barcelona. The second edition\, "Small Em
 bodied Data\," centres on the concept of classification -- approached thro
 ugh machine learning\, data science\, algorithmic systems\, and questions 
 of who designs classifiers\, under what ethical codes\, and to what end. T
 he biennial brings classification into dialogue with its previous themes o
 f Small Data (community-defined\, intentional data collection and analysis
 ) and Embodiment (bodily experience as a foundation of situated\, sensory 
 knowledge). Both academic and non-academic contributions are welcome. FORM
 ATS ACCEPTED: Oral Presentations (20 minutes\; artistic practice\, artisti
 c research\, or academic research projects\; may be video-recorded for a p
 ublic archive and developed into short papers)\; Performances (20-30 minut
 es\; must engage with the physical body\, stage\, and technology\; complet
 e works\, including previously presented work\; takes place in a multipurp
 ose space with technical support). SUBMISSION REQUIREMENTS: online form wi
 th abstract (max 1\,000 characters)\, professional biography (max 1\,000 c
 haracters)\, and link to representative materials (3-5 images\; video and 
 technical rider required for performances). HONORARIA: oral presentations 
 €100\; performances €400\; invoice required in both cases. Participant
 s must follow the event's code of conduct. Event runs 26-28 November 2026 
 at UOC Poblenou campus and Convent de Sant Agustí\, Barcelona. Deadline: 
 7 September 2026. Submit at https://hibrides.axolot.cat/opencall.html.\n\n
 Organisation: Axolot.cat collective and DARTS research group\, Universitat
  Oberta de Catalunya (UOC)\nLocation: Barcelona\, Spain\; UOC Poblenou cam
 pus and Convent de Sant Agustí. In-person attendance required.\nAward: Or
 al presentations: €100 honorarium (invoice required). Performances: €4
 00 honorarium (invoice required). No submission fee.\nDuration: Festival r
 uns 26-28 November 2026.\n\nMore: https://hibrides.axolot.cat/opencall.htm
 l?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://hibrides.axolot.cat/opencall.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
